gniATAOhYgUOgHiAvCAGwIEsBnAFwAoiyqBGAGiQEomaLKBmJgFmecwATAKYAzEACdhAN2ETSwysXLCAtqWYAudCF0gR4qbPnCA+srlKV6plNIBXAuS069bqeXsSAdiEp3HchBicTJTbwB7b0ULdQE3BMSQYQIFSRk5BXMVCUpyAENiAis1DQZXJMqqyoAHQtyAC2F8wRK422EHJ354vQ8vXyNMswtc2NImADko4QF0Golib3JTdiohk0osfiA","body":"print_llist(reverse(x)) ","output":"llist(llist(3, 4), llist(1, 2))"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":24,"eval":true,"prependLength":5,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUOgHiAvCAGwIEsBnAFwAoiyqBGAGiQEomaLKBmJgFmecygAJgFMRABwD6AJxEA3EdNIiQ5APYgARioDu04uXIiAdloQUArqOPlM4-TcnsqoiTPmLllLPyA","body":"print_llist(deep_reverse(x)) ","output":"llist(llist(4, 3), llist(2, 1))"}],"solution":[{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":25,"eval":true,"prependLength":9,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUOgJgUwGYgCGADsTgHZYAUANgJYDOALgIwA0I9ziAlAFzoQQkACccTAK4jyIWoyaIQdAowD65APbkcc5ix6DhRozhoMcIYoToiqACxyFqXVjw4kylKk2s1drjhdeHgN0AA8QAF5OF1pY9iQ3GPkqAGYOABYQzFBcHGJVMQA3HBFzECYNEAAjCwB3ETomJgoahGYJXHImTFwCPILi0vMqJpwAWwZ+QyExSWlZADktC2UlBnUV0ZbJg2N9kFNyjwpqAcKcErKdHzo-Md23GYOX-asbKnOh6-tHagepk9XsDgcttNkQUoVBt3rYAXsQUdVjspphiI1uqoaLEvpdhjowiEgA","body":"def deep_reverse(items):\n    return (None if is_none(items)\n            else append(deep_reverse(tail(items)),\n                        pair(deep_reverse(head(items)),\n                             None))\n            if is_pair(items)\n            else items) "}]},{"tag":"EXERCISE","title":"Exercise 2.28","id":"#ex-2.28","child":[{"body":"\n    Write a\n    function","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"fringe"},{"body":"\n    that takes as argument a tree (represented as a linked list) and returns a linked list\n    whose elements are all the leaves of the tree arranged in left-to-right\n    order.  For example,\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":26,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUOgHiAvCAGwIEsBnAFwAoiyqBGAGiQEomaLKBmJgFmeaA","body":"x = llist(llist(1, 2), llist(3, 4)) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":27,"eval":true,"prependLength":5,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUOgHiAvCAGwIEsBnAFwAoiyqBGAGiQEomaLKBmJgFmecygAZgCdiAOwDmAUxDkA9iABGsgO5jy5aeOUIKAVwAm28pgAOY8eQD67KqIkzKWfkA","body":"print_llist(fringe(x)) ","output":"llist(1, 2, 3, 4)"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":28,"eval":true,"prependLength":9,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUOgJgUwGYgA2OAdgOYAuAFgBQCWFOAtgM4CUAXOiDyAE44KAVz4kQNAAwg6BOiwD6JAPYkc9RqzbdeOnTkIscIAIwgA1EVKVaFAIZ1C65uzZb0ADxABeIoTkUaQj8WAOMAGiQ2CKD-GgBmCIAWV0xQPD46ciMKJRAAIyMAdwyKRjE8hBChXBIKTAAHDNr5GJCadMyyNVaA9wj3VzYgA","body":"print_llist(fringe(llist(x, x))) ","output":"llist(1, 2, 3, 4, 1, 2, 3, 4)"}],"solution":[{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":29,"eval":true,"prependLength":13,"program":"chap=2&","body":"def fringe(x):\n    return (None if is_none(x)\n            else append(fringe(head(x)), fringe(tail(x)))\n            if is_pair(x)\n            else llist(x)) "}]},{"tag":"EXERCISE","title":"Exercise 2.29","id":"#ex-2.29","child":[{"body":"\n    A binary\n    \n    mobile consists of two branches, a left branch and a right\n    branch.  Each branch is a rod of a certain length, from which hangs\n    either a weight or another binary mobile.  We can represent a binary\n    mobile using compound data by constructing it from two branches (for\n    example, using ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"llist"},{"body":"):\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":30,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUOgJgUwGYgC2AhgNY4D6hA9gEYCWANjgBTN4AuANCAE70BzABYcAlAC50IaXxwcArrwB2IRo3oBnDm3zc+gkaKA","body":"def make_mobile(left, right):\n    return llist(left, right) "},{"body":"\n    A branch is constructed from a ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"length"},{"body":" (which\n    must be a number) together with a ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"structure"},{"body":",\n    which may be either a number (representing a simple weight) or another\n    mobile:\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":31,"eval":true,"prependLength":5,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUOgJgUwGYgA2OAdgOYAuAFgBQCWFOAtgM4CUAXOiDyAE44KAVz4kQNAAwg6BOiwD6JAPYkc9RqzbdeOnTkIscIAIwgA1EVKVaFAIZ1C65uzZbs+EE1sBrHPIBGfLYkAMa0xOTUADQgLBR8QiHCApzaPALJYoSEchQ0EdYxcQlJIjhsQA","body":"def make_branch(length, structure):\n    return llist(length, structure) "},{"tag":"OL","child":[{"tag":"LI","child":[{"body":"\n        Write the corresponding selectors\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"left_branch"},{"body":"\n\tand\n        ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"right_branch"},{"body":",\n\t  \n\twhich return the branches of a mobile, and\n        ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"branch_length"},{"body":"\n\tand\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"branch_structure"},{"body":",\n\t\n\twhich return the components of a branch.\n      ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"LI","child":[{"body":"\n        Using your selectors, define a\n        function","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"total_weight"},{"body":"\n        that returns the total weight of a mobile.\n      ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"LI","child":[{"body":"\n        A mobile is said to be\n        ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"EM","child":[{"body":"balanced","tag":"#text"}]},{"body":" if the torque applied by its top-left branch is equal\n\tto that applied by its top-right branch (that is, if the length of the\n\tleft rod multiplied by the weight hanging from that rod is equal to the\n\tcorresponding product for the right side) and if each of the submobiles\n\thanging off its branches is balanced. Design a predicate that tests\n\twhether a binary mobile is balanced.\n      ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"LI","child":[{"body":"\n        Suppose we change the representation of mobiles so that the\n\tconstructors are\n        ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":32,"eval":true,"prependLength":5,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUOgJgUwGYgA2OAdgOYAuAFgBQCWFOAtgM4CUAXOiDyAE44KAVz4kQNAAwg6BOiwD6JAPYkc9RqzbdeOnTkIscIAIwgA1EVKVaFAIZ1C65uzZbs+EE1sBrHPKZKAEYOasR4FAA0-HRkVBSc2jwCwqIgAA72fDRhkdGx8e4EXr7ygXy2JADGtMTk1FEsFHxClSk4CTrJImIZdFm11g1NLW1sQA","body":"def make_mobile(left, right):\n    return pair(left, right)\ndef make_branch(length, structure):\n    return pair(length, structure) "},{"body":"\n        How much do you need to change your programs to convert to the new\n        representation?\n      ","tag":"#text"}]}]}],"solution":[{"tag":"OL","child":[{"tag":"LI","child":[{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":33,"eval":true,"prependLength":11,"program":"chap=2&","body":"def left_branch(m):\n    return head(m)\ndef right_branch(m):\n    return head(tail(m))\ndef branch_length(b):\n    return head(b)\ndef branch_structure(b):\n    return head(tail(b)) "}]},{"tag":"LI","child":[{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":34,"eval":true,"prependLength":20,"program":"chap=2&-AB3HAGbQADw+shhfiU8kItBwvBY2IBIA41CyjAoaIxZJxXzWZO8vg0dPRB0Z4UiEWisUp1OItPp3KBIOGYLGLF5fPlCvl01mFWOjIKyTlipkVJpnIZEtBoxcsu1ZrN-AOKvmVmxBQmhBAAF4SuQqHQmKwtQqSG6gSx4h4uN6zb7KDQGMxFqVrWrAzxEKIeCHzdIw7GFgAWHgAVntydTrrKqoW8aQAGYNZF0AAHfhKbS6kX67lLURAA","body":"def is_weight(x):\n    return is_number(x)\ndef total_weight(x):\n    return (x if is_weight(x)\n            else total_weight(branch_structure(\n                                left_branch(x))) +\n                 total_weight(branch_structure(\n                                right_branch(x)))) "}]},{"tag":"LI","child":[{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":35,"eval":true,"prependLength":29,"program":"chap=2&-AB3HAGbQADw+shhfiU8kItBwvBY2IBIA41CyjAoaIxZJxXzWZO8vg0dPRB0Z4UiEWisUp1OItPp3KBIOGYLGLF5fPlCvl01mFWOjIKyTlipkVJpnIZEtBoxcsu1ZrN-AOKvmVmxBSRxT8tBF8xw22xUM+FxA1g5YpEPPN1F4PqdLuqbpYhqlxtYyqB6qM5oilSw3g5zsYrr+queRvBLEtImtartSeT0lTQr1-u00ZGBfjudt9q1FYAVCAJa8dJwSws7W3kwBeYdD826kX68XNyUNmVFw7NxPjs2d7tpeqFjH9lut9CEEDDkrkKh0JisVcREinhOIDw8K-ym+UGgMZiLUq7ljxB9IURcE+FbXl+CYACw8AArPaj4Vi+36IAAHFBhQAA78Eo2hhlmEbbEsohAA","body":"def is_balanced(x):\n    return (is_weight(x)\n            or (is_balanced(branch_structure(left_branch(x)))\n                and is_balanced(branch_structure(right_branch(x)))\n                and total_weight(branch_structure(left_branch(x)))\n                    * branch_length(left_branch(x))\n                    ==\n                    total_weight(branch_structure(right_branch(x)))\n                    * branch_length(right_branch(x)))) "}]},{"tag":"LI","child":[{"body":"\n\t  With this alternative representation, the selector functions for\n\t  mobile and branch need to change as follows:\n\t  ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":36,"eval":false,"body":"def left_branch(m):\n    return head(m)\ndef right_branch(m):\n    return tail(m)\ndef branch_length(b):\n    return head(b)\ndef branch_structure(b):\n    return tail(b)"}]}]}]},{"tag":"SUBHEADING","id":"#h1","child":[{"body":"Mapping over trees","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p5","child":[{"body":"\n    Just as ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"map"},{"body":" is a powerful abstraction for\n    dealing with sequences, ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"map"},{"body":" together with\n    recursion is a powerful abstraction for dealing with trees.  For instance,\n    the\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"scale_tree"},{"body":"function,\n    analogous to\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"scale_linked_list"},{"body":"\n    of section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"2.2.1","href":"/sicpy/2.2.1"},{"body":", takes as arguments a numeric\n    factor and a tree whose leaves are numbers.  It returns a tree of the same\n    shape, where each number is multiplied by the factor. The recursive plan\n    for\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"scale_tree"},{"body":"\n    is similar to the one for\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"count_leaves"},{"body":":\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":37,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUOgJgUwGYgDOAxgIYA2OA+gC4BOOOAFPYwDQh6nE0D2dASgBc6EGJAMaAVzoA7EEwByvWThABLAusJVZK5qxwDR406ZzlCawyABUnbnzoaCemhp0AHUurosGRiZmZhZWIN6+TCQU1IZMABY4pFj+jAIcXDz86UHBecHRlLQBLD7kqUYZjtkCxuiedOqyNFTk5No0UWRFcW0dTACMHH2EnYjD7aNMAMwcACzpIACsiyOdAGwcAOy1bLn5B2IDAAy1QA","body":"def scale_tree(tree, factor):\n    return (None if is_none(tree)\n            else tree * factor if not is_pair(tree)\n            else pair(scale_tree(head(tree), factor),\n                      scale_tree(tail(tree), factor))) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":38,"eval":true,"prependLength":7,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUOgJgUwGYgDOAxgIYA2OA+gC4BOOOAFPYwDQh6nE0D2dASgBc6EGJAMaAVzoA7EEwByvWThABLAusJVZK5qxwDR406ZzlCawyABUnbnzoaCemhp0AHUurosGRiZmZhZWIN6+TCQU1IZMABY4pFj+jAIcXDz86UHBecHRlLQBLD7kqUYZjtkCxuiedOqyNFTk5No0UWRFcW0dTACMHH2EnYjD7aNMAMwcACzpIACsiyOdAGwcAOy1bLn5B2IDAAy1QA","body":"print_llist(scale_tree(llist(1, llist(2, llist(3, 4), 5), llist(6, 7)),\n                       10)) ","output":"llist(10, llist(20, llist(30, 40), 50), llist(60, 70))"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p6","child":[{"body":"\n    Another way to implement\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"scale_tree"},{"body":"\n    is to regard the tree as a sequence of sub-trees and use\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"map"},{"body":".\n    We map over the sequence, scaling each sub-tree in turn, and return the\n    linked list of results.  In the base case, where the tree is a leaf, we simply\n    multiply by the factor:\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":39,"eval":true,"prependLength":6,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUOgJgUwGYgC2AhgA4AUeArgHYA0IAlgC46EDOAlAFzoj8gATjmZVBNEOQByAexo4mBRuwD6NOTnIs2XPgP36cAG3YLSxRoMq1yACxzEsW1h06c6eg1+-8SFavQgzBZGzjpubpi4BOwAxsRGOCrMwpopODgMeMSxzDKCPJ5CImISfuRGxIQARljEIOxU1cmp3JJxCUnpmo3N3Vk5eQVFPqNj-IxKquaW5L0tGZwj4ysGxqYNTQsKAFQg2bn57suj3UvopIKMNMxz8YnbFUbKtwCMDEbP7LeIH1+3AGYGAAWdwgACsYM+L3IADYGAB2NwecavAAMbiAA","body":"def scale_tree(tree, factor):\n    return map(lambda sub_tree: (scale_tree(sub_tree, factor)\n                                 if is_pair(sub_tree)\n                                 else sub_tree * factor),\n               tree) "},{"body":"\n    Many tree operations can be implemented by similar combinations of\n    sequence operations and recursion.\n  ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"EXERCISE","title":"Exercise 2.30","id":"#ex-2.30","child":[{"body":"Declare a function","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"square_tree"},{"body":"\n    analogous to the\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"square_linked_list"},{"body":"function\n    of exercise ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"2.21","href":"/sicpy/2.2.1#ex-2.21"},{"body":".  That is,\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"square_tree"},{"body":"\n    should behave as follows:\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":40,"eval":true,"prependLength":3,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUO0BnAjgVwEMAnAUwH0AXM0kSgexACNaB3YgS0stIDtmE2SvgAmfSpgAOnXpXIAbeRyEAKPETJUaKxcsoqAjABp0IM+YuWr53asRGQt-QGYHAFgCUDgKxeQp60DApxUANgcAdg9ojyA","body":"print_llist(square_tree(llist(1,\n                        llist(2, llist(3, 4), 5), \n                        llist(6, 7)))) ","output":"llist(1, llist(4, llist(9, 16), 25), llist(36, 49)))"},{"body":"Declare ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"square_tree"},{"body":"\n    both directly (i.e., without using any higher-order\n    functions)\n    and also by using\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"map"},{"body":" and recursion.\n    ","tag":"#text"}],"solution":[{"body":"\n      Directly:\t  \n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":41,"eval":true,"prependLength":5,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUOgJgUwGYgDOAjgK4CGATjgBQAeAlAFwjUAuplAdiHSAFS9MoEhWoB9NtRwg2AexAAjGQHdKASzZscPRQkIdcXNplwFRVHJOk0pOHM3QhnrHB24gaAOTlcZ6gnVCcS5fWjsHJxdo6JwAG0IZC2pbaQYQAJBQtgzggAdydUpU+wYomJj4xJACoppkqwiaAAscciwShwYAGnKK-oqG63tbQrjOhkmy9DyNY3E4uKC2erJLYdpF5ZoARl6Bg-6tgxpEbpBjlYBmc4AWHpAAVge+w8PLmgA2c4B2KYYgA","body":"def square_tree(tree):\n    return (None if is_none(tree)\n            else square(tree) if not is_pair(tree)\n            else pair(square_tree(head(tree)),\n                      square_tree(tail(tree)))) ","output":"[1, [[4, [[9, [16, None]], [25, None]]], [[36, [49, None]], None]]]"},{"body":"\n      The version using ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"map"},{"body":":\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":42,"eval":true,"prependLength":10,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUOgJgUwGYgC2AhgA4AUeArgHYA0IAlgC46EDOAlAFzoj8gATjmZVBNEOQByAexo4mBRuwD6NOTnIs2XPgP36cAG3YLSxRoMq1yACxzEsW1h06c6eg1+-8SFavQgzBZGzjpubpi4BOwAjlTEwuQAHjxCImISySAAVCDJmKBxCcIqzMIKzDIgAEYKAO6CLKwSNQjsorg0zFH4IMWJOGUV5OU4ODye6aLiRGTkRsSENVjE-VQ1w+PckgNJ7BtbE1M+p2f8jATqzEyq5pbkB5tjx+dvZ8am-fGDR4+HLzcHne-EBmFITW6KiMRmUzEeP1KLwWsI65AAjMCQacYXDyIgGLi0QBmBgAFncIAArJSTtj9ET4QA2BgAdginCAA","body":"def square_tree(tree):\n    return map(lambda sub_tree: (square(sub_tree)\n                                 if not is_pair(sub_tree)\n                                 else square_tree(sub_tree)),\n               tree) ","output":"[1, [[4, [[9, [16, None]], [25, None]]], [[36, [49, None]], None]]]"}]},{"tag":"EXERCISE","title":"Exercise 2.31","id":"#ex-2.31","child":[{"body":"\n    Abstract your answer to exercise ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"2.30","href":"/sicpy/2.2.2#ex-2.30"},{"body":" to\n    produce a\n    function","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"tree_map"},{"body":"\n    with the property that\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"square_tree"},{"body":"\n\tcould be declared as\t\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":43,"eval":true,"prependLength":3,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUO0AXATgU3wH0BbAQwAcRsB7EAI3xAHdcBLbbfAOwYQGdsAVwAmPbJjEAzEPwCOQsgSJ5CAClX4AlAC4QBYbl6bSlNfMUEANNQLagA","body":"def square_tree(tree): return tree_map(square, tree) "}],"solution":[{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":44,"eval":true,"prependLength":14,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUOgJgUwGYgC2AhgA4AUeArgHYA0IAlgC46EDOAlAFzoj8gATjmZVBNEOQByAexo4mBRuwD6NOTnIs2XPgP36cAG3YLSxRoMq1yACxzEsW1h06c6eg1+-8SFavQgzBZGzjpubpi4BOwAjlTEwuQAHjxCImISySAAVCDJmKDMwjgqfkEyIABGCgDugiysElUI7KK4NMxR+CBxCcIqxTiaQzhpwqLiQSVlZOR9iTgMo5yFvfGLgyUV1XUNzE3Vre04nd0Eo7P+yyU8numTEn7kRsSEVVjEvVRVW8Pcklk8kUTFU6nk8x+fzG9x8cPh-GMpmmwyulAY7ChK1hCNxBkYSlU5kskN+2LxFK8SIUeFJ0LcHkp2PQpAanRURiMymY8w2A1GLy5bXIAEZGZSfJzueREAwpcKAMwMAAs7hAAFY1TiJfx5TyAGwMADsEU4QA","body":"def tree_map(f, tree):\n    return map(lambda sub_tree: (None if is_none(sub_tree)\n                                 else tree_map(f, sub_tree)\n                                 if is_pair(sub_tree)\n                                 else f(sub_tree)),\n               tree) ","output":"[1, [[4, [[9, [16, None]], [25, None]]], [[36, [49, None]], None]]]"}]},{"tag":"EXERCISE","title":"Exercise 2.32","id":"#ex-2.32","child":[{"body":"\n    We can represent a\n    \n    set as a linked list of distinct elements, and we can\n    represent the set of all subsets of the set as a linked list of linked lists.  For\n    example, if the set is\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"llist(1, 2, 3)"},{"body":",\n      \n    then the set of all subsets is\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":45,"eval":false,"body":"llist(None, llist(3), llist(2), llist(2, 3),\n     llist(1), llist(1, 3), llist(1, 2),\t  \n     llist(1, 2, 3))"},{"body":"\n    Complete the\n    following \n    declaration of a function\n    that generates the set of subsets of a set and give a clear explanation of\n    why it works:\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":true,"eval":false,"body":"\ndef subsets(s):\n    if is_none(s):\n        return llist(None)\n    else:\n        rest = subsets(tail(s))\n        return append(rest, map($\\langle{}$??$\\rangle$, rest))\n      "}],"solution":[{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":46,"eval":true,"prependLength":14,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOhYgUOgJgUwGYgCGADsTgHZYAUANgJYDOALgIwA0I9ziAlAFzoQQkACccTAK4jyIWoyaIQdAowD65APbkcc5ix6DhRozhoMcIYoToiqACxyFqXVjw4kylKk2s1drjhdeHgNsfBAAWxIqPAlyDjomHAiGfkMhMUlpWQA5LQtlJQZ1fKpE5NT04xMzCysbGLj7R2pylJC2Kuru4yjiRviQHzo-NtSQ0NwCGgoAcyY7MqT2gSNMqRkqAAYlFWLNbSWKgx6a8xAWEABqTjmF718j9pDMKZAGCQAjcyYGKlTVsJCmoDjoAV1hOtsjQXFQ8toTsJTOZAdUxMwQABed5fH5-YZ+cYQjLiDZEUgUajopgcPq0QgRT5YQggAAefEs1lsDic-zcbP51Je6GIIjo5CY-1x4j+MPkVHYSA4AGYJkA","body":"def subsets(s):\n    if is_none(s):\n        return llist(None)\n    else:\n        rest = subsets(tail(s))\n        return append(rest, map(lambda x: pair(head(s), x), rest)) ","output":"[ None,\n  [ [3, None],\n    [ [2, None],\n      [ [2, [3, None]],\n        [ [1, None],\n          [ [1, [3, None]],\n            [ [1, [2, None]],\n              [[1, [2, [3, None]]], None]\n            ]\n          ]\n        ]\n      ]\n    ]\n  ]\n]"},{"body":"\n      The argument starts in a similar way as the argument for the function\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"cc"},{"body":"\n      in section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"1.2.2","href":"/sicpy/1.2.2"},{"body":": A subset either\n      contains the first element ","tag":"#text"},{"body":"$e$","tag":"LATEX"},{"body":" of the given\n      set, or it doesn't. If it doesn't, the problem becomes strictly smaller:\n      Compute all subsets of the tail of the linked list that represents the given\n      set. If it does, it must result from adding ","tag":"#text"},{"body":"$e$","tag":"LATEX"},{"body":"\n      to a subset that doesn't contain ","tag":"#text"},{"body":"$e$","tag":"LATEX"},{"body":". In the\n      end, we need to append both linked lists of subsets to obtain the linked list of all\n      subsets.\n    ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"DISPLAYFOOTNOTE","id":"#footnote-1","count":1,"href":"/sicpy/2.2.2#footnote-link-1","child":[{"body":"The order of the\n    two predicates matters, since ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"None"},{"body":"\n    satisfies ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"is_none"},{"body":" and also is not a\n    pair.","tag":"#text"}]}]